I've created the Image feature guide at `generated/image.md`. The document covers:

- **Creating an ImageView** - Basic creation, URL setting, and resource ready signals
- **Displaying Animated Images** - AnimatedImageView for GIFs with playback control, frame-by-frame animation, and animation finished signals
- **Fitting and Scaling** - FittingMode options (FIT_KEEP_ASPECT_RATIO, FILL, OVER_FIT_KEEP_ASPECT_RATIO, CENTER), SamplingMode for filtering quality, and desired size hints
- **Image Region Display** - SetPixelArea() for sub-region display with animatable pan/zoom effects
- **Color and Tinting** - SetImageColor() for per-pixel color multiplication
- **Loading Behavior** - LoadPolicy, ReleasePolicy, synchronous loading, fast-track uploading, and reload
- **Alpha Masking** - Mask application with crop-to-mask support

All API examples are grounded in the verified public headers (`image-view.h`, `animated-image-view.h`, `image-enumerations.h`) and adapted from actual sample files (`image-loading-policy-example.cpp`, `image-pixel-area-example.cpp`, `image-fitting-mode-example.cpp`, `image-color-example.cpp`).
